From 6d5f30e7140481b85367aaf153ca342494d4a3fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Prajw <prajw@trivartatech>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 13:43:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat: staff QR badge exports + in-app QR display
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three additions covering the printing and the on-phone display side
of staff QR attendance.

WEB — bulk badge generation
  • New app/Exports/StaffQRExport.php — Excel sheet with embedded PNG
    QR codes per staff (mirrors StudentQRExport).
  • New PDF print sheet at resources/views/exports/staff-badges.blade.php
    — 8 badges per A4 page, each with school header, staff name,
    designation, department, employee_id pill, phone, and a 26mm QR
    on the right.
  • StaffController gets exportQrCodesExcel() and exportQrCodesPdf().
  • Routes added BEFORE Route::resource('staff', ...) so 'qr-codes' is
    not eaten by the {staff} route binding:
      GET /school/staff/qr-codes/excel
      GET /school/staff/qr-codes/pdf
  • Two new buttons in Pages/School/Staff/Index.vue header:
      "QR Badges PDF"  → print-ready
      "QR Excel"       → spreadsheet with embedded QRs

  All QRs encode url('/q/staff/<employee_id>') — the same shape the
  mobile rapid-scan endpoint accepts via its /staff/<id> regex.

MOBILE — in-app QR display
  • New endpoint GET /api/mobile/staff-qr/me returns the current
    staff member's QR as a base64 PNG data URI plus name, designation,
    department, employee_id, school name, and the encoded URL.
  • Generated server-side via Endroid\QrCode (already installed for
    student QRs). No new client-side dep needed.
  • New screen src/screens/staff/MyQrScreen.js — displays the QR card
    with the staff's details. Caches the response in AsyncStorage so
    the QR is shown instantly on next open and works offline.
  • Wired into both AdminNavigator and TeacherNavigator as a "My QR"
    tab (qr-code-outline icon). Lives next to "My Punch".

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
